          <figcaption class="image-caption" style="box-sizing: content-box; color: #808080; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: -.15px; line-height: 20px; margin-top: 8px; padding-left: 15%; padding-right: 15%; text-align: center; width: 70%;">
           <em>
            <a href="https://substack.com/redirect/bc6bdf34-aefd-4a9a-9d5e-ef263766042a?j=eyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel="" style="text-decoration: underline;">
             Casey Handmer on X
            </a>
           </em>
          </figcaption>
         </figure>
        </div>
        <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         The grand challenge of, and incentives to prevent, the climate crisis have pulled in some of the smartest people in the world to use all the tools at humanity\xe2\x80\x99s disposal to avoid disaster, and in the process, beat the boss and advance to the next level of ENERGY: The Game.
        </p>
        <h3 class="header-with-anchor-widget" style="-moz-appearance: optimizelegibility; -moz-osx-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-appearance: optimizelegibility; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; appearance: optimizelegibility; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-family: 'SF Compact Display', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 1.375em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.16em; margin: 1em 0 0.625em 0; position: relative;">
         <strong>
          Have Kids
         </strong>
        </h3>
        <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         Look, I tried to simplify millions of years of history and some very complex, multi-causal events into one, clean narrative. I\xe2\x80\x99m missing important details, even getting some wrong.
        </p>
        <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         But from this zoomed out view, the period that we\xe2\x80\x99re living through isn\xe2\x80\x99t a tragedy, it\xe2\x80\x99s a trial, and it will be a triumph.
        </p>
        <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         Without the climate crisis, we would likely have ridden fossil fuels until it was too late. At that point, we wouldn\xe2\x80\x99t have been able to power a growing population or increasingly powerful machines. We might not have had the resources to develop, produce, and scale the next generation of energy sources at all. Without the climate crisis, the future might have been bleak. That zero-sum, negative growth world would have been a bad one to bring kids into.
        </p>
        <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         Because of it, the world has accelerated the development and deployment of technologies like solar, fission, and fusion. We\xe2\x80\x99re not out of the woods, but we have the tools to get out.
        </p>
        <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         The moment we begin to reverse the effects of climate change, we\xe2\x80\x99ll have broken through to the next level, one in which we can manufacture energy and consume as much of it as we would like without fear of killing the planet. That is enormous and unprecedented.
        </p>
        <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         There will certainly be new problems and challenges. Utopia isn\xe2\x80\x99t real, and we wouldn\xe2\x80\x99t want it to be.
        </p>
        <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         But if history is a guide, the next level in ENERGY will transform and improve society in ways that are impossible to predict from our current vantage point, just as it would have been impossible to sketch the Industrial Revolution by looking at the Newcomen Steam Engine.
        </p>
        <div class="captioned-image-container-static" style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 32px auto;">
         <figure style="margin: 0 auto; width: 100%;">
          <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="image-wrapper" data-component-name="Image2ToDOMStatic" style="mso-padding-alt: 1em 0 1.6em;" width="100%">
           <tbody>
            <tr>
             <td style="text-align: center;">
             </td>
             <td align="left" class="content" style="text-align: center;" width="908">
              <a class="image-link" href="https://substack.com/redirect/30dbc6c3-2344-49cf-9690-b2d508fd06a7?j=eyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel="" style="align-items: center; border: none; display: block; flex-direction: column; height: auto; margin: 0; padding: 0; position: relative; text-decoration: none; width: auto;" target="_blank">
               <img alt="" class="wide-image" data-attrs='{"src":"https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/48978fcc-141e-443f-b66d-d71741311cfe_908x645.png","srcNoWatermark":null,"fullscreen":null,"imageSize":null,"height":645,"width":908,"resizeWidth":null,"bytes":null,"alt":null,"title":null,"type":null,"href":null,"belowTheFold":true,"topImage":false,"internalRedirect":null}' height="390.69383259911893" src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1816,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F48978fcc-141e-443f-b66d-d71741311cfe_908x645.png" style="-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic; border: none !important; display: block; height: auto; margin: 0 auto; margin-bottom: 0; max-width: 100% !important; vertical-align: middle; width: auto !important;" width="550"/>
              </a>
             </td>
             <td style="text-align: center;">
             </td>
            </tr>
           </tbody>
          </table>
          <figcaption class="image-caption" style="box-sizing: content-box; color: #808080; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: -.15px; line-height: 20px; margin-top: 8px; padding-left: 15%; padding-right: 15%; text-align: center; width: 70%;">
           <em>
            Our World in Data
           </em>
          </figcaption>
         </figure>
        </div>
        <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         If we get this right, our kids will live in a world that\xe2\x80\x99s more abundant and more ethical than the one we inhabit today. They\xe2\x80\x99ll look back at 2023 the same way we look back at 1712: wouldn\xe2\x80\x99t want to live there, but thankful for the contributions of the people who did.
        </p>
        <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         Climate change is real. It\xe2\x80\x99s our current Boss. Defeating it will require deft gameplay from millions of people, governments, and businesses.
        </p>
        <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         But it doesn\xe2\x80\x99t spell inevitable doom, either. Humans are incredibly adaptable, and against all odds, we\xe2\x80\x99ve created exactly the right tools to defeat it and unlock the next level at exactly the right time.
        </p>
        <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         Having kids isn\xe2\x80\x99t the problem; it\xe2\x80\x99s the solution. It\xe2\x80\x99s exactly because people who lived in much worse conditions than we do decided to have kids that we have the ultimate weapon in this game: human creativity.
        </p>
        <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         Whatever challenges await on the next level, we\xe2\x80\x99ll need all the kids we can get to solve them.
        </p>
        <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         <span>
          So don\xe2\x80\x99t listen to the doom and gloom. It\xe2\x80\x99s counterproductive, depressing, and evil. It prioritizes clicks over your happiness and uses
         </span>
         <a href="https://substack.com/redirect/83450b59-295f-44ef-8e5e-9e3d68af163b?j=eyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel="" style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">
          fear to sell ads
         </a>
         <span>
          . The people pretending to be ethical by being pessimistic are not the good guys; they\xe2\x80\x99re villains in this game.
         </span>
        </p>
        <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         But villains can be useful, too. They\xe2\x80\x99re part of the game. If that fear has motivated some of our best people to join the fight to beat the boss and unlock the next level, humanity is better off for it.
        </p>
        <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         Just don\xe2\x80\x99t let it depress you into hopeless inaction, right when things are about to get really good. Don\xe2\x80\x99t let it stop you from bringing kids into this world.
        </p>
        <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         If we\xe2\x80\x99re lucky, we might be alive to experience some of the wonders of this next level. I certainly hope to be.
        </p>
        <div class="captioned-image-container-static" style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 32px auto;">
         <figure style="margin: 0 auto; width: 100%;">
          <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="image-wrapper" data-component-name="Image2ToDOMStatic" style="mso-padding-alt: 1em 0 1.6em;" width="100%">
           <tbody>
            <tr>
             <td style="text-align: center;">
             </td>
             <td align="left" class="content" style="text-align: center;" width="908">
              <a class="image-link" href="https://substack.com/redirect/7c3d7377-4daf-4ddc-944f-a4c29f8f30b1?j=eyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel="" style="align-items: center; border: none; display: block; flex-direction: column; height: auto; margin: 0; padding: 0; position: relative; text-decoration: none; width: auto;" target="_blank">
               <img alt="" class="wide-image" data-attrs='{"src":"https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/32867789-d8e7-42bb-9534-161ee2c4fb56_908x547.png","srcNoWatermark":null,"fullscreen":null,"imageSize":null,"height":547,"width":908,"resizeWidth":null,"bytes":918535,"alt":null,"title":null,"type":"image/png","href":null,"belowTheFold":true,"topImage":false,"internalRedirect":null}' height="331.3325991189427" src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1816,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F32867789-d8e7-42bb-9534-161ee2c4fb56_908x547.png" style="-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic; border: none !important; display: block; height: auto; margin: 0 auto; margin-bottom: 0; max-width: 100% !important; vertical-align: middle; width: auto !important;" width="550"/>
              </a>
             </td>
             <td style="text-align: center;">
             </td>
