           </tbody>
          </table>
         </figure>
        </div>
        <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         But I\xe2\x80\x99m almost certain that our kids will be, and I am so excited for them. What a time to be alive!
        </p>
        <div class="footnote" data-component-name="FootnoteToDOMStatic" style="align-items: baseline; border-top: solid 1px rgba(196, 202, 204, 0.5); display: flex; flex-direction: row; font-size: 90%; line-height: 26px; margin-bottom: 0; padding-top: 1.5em;">
         <span class="footnote-number" style="display: block; margin-right: 6px; min-width: 24px;">
          1
         </span>
         <div class="footnote-content" style="display: block; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;">
          <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0; min-width: 10px;">
           <em>
            Not all of you, of course. You might have very good non-climate-related reasons to not have kids. You might be too young or too old. You might not have the means to add another mouth to feed at the moment. There are a number of valid reasons to not have kids right now, but the climate isn\xe2\x80\x99t one of them.
           </em>
          </p>
          <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0; min-width: 10px;">
          </p>
         </div>
        </div>
